    <section anchor="security" title="Security Considerations">
      <t>
        Metadata Filter reveals preference intent by peers. Deploy primarily in iBGP, and restrict which peers may advertise Metadata Filter entries.
        Omission of metadata does not affect reachability but can affect path-selection at the receiver; operators should audit
        Metadata Filter policy, enable change logging/dampening, and apply session protections (e.g., GTSM, TCP-AO) where appropriate.
      </t>
    </section>

	
